A teenager is in a critical condition after she was hit by a car in Darvel, East Ayrshire. Teenager hit by car in Darvel in critical condition A teenager is in a critical condition after she was hit by a car in Darvel, East Ayrshire.
The 17-year-old was hit by a blue Mercedes CLA as she crossed the A71 at West Main Street at 18:44 on Friday. 
She was taken to Crosshouse Hospital in Kilmarnock where her condition was described as critical but stable. 
The 23-year-old car driver and his passenger were uninjured. Police want to trace the driver of a white van which stopped after the incident. 
Sgt Ian Thornton, of Police Scotland, said: &quot;We understand that there was a white van which was stopped at the junction of Burns Road, directly after the pedestrian was struck. 
&quot;We ask that the driver get in touch with information which may be relevant.&quot;
Sgt Thornton asked anyone with information to contact police.
 